results.title: Infinity Gauntlet (1991) #4
results.description:
Wolverine, broken! The Scarlet Witch, incinerated! She-Hulk and Namor,
buried alive! The Vision, ripped apart! Thor, shattered! Iron Man,
beheaded! Cyclops, suffocated! When Earth's heroes attack, Thanos takes
the kid gloves off -- but leaves the god-making Infinity Gauntlet on!

textObjects.text:
Wolverine, broken! The Scarlet Witch, incinerated! She-Hulk and Namor,
buried alive! The Vision, ripped apart! Thor, shattered! Iron Man,
beheaded! Cyclops, suffocated! When Earth's heroes attack, Thanos takes
the kid gloves off -- but leaves the god-making Infinity Gauntlet on!

After dealing with the deaths of half the universe, Earth's remaining heroes (and Dr. Doom) gather together to take the fight to Thanos, the infinitely powerful madman responsible for the whole mess. Guess how that turns out?

results.title: Infinity Gauntlet (1991) #1
results.description:
Seeking to impress the Mistress Death, who returned him to life, Thanos
has gained control over the Infinity Gauntlet -- making him an
all-powerful god! With Mephisto as his familiar, Thanos wipes out half
of the life in the universe with a snap of his fingers! What will Earth
do when half its the heroes are killed?

One of the most epic Marvel stories ever told deserves a cover that does it justice.  George Perez delivers in spades.
